25:10.840 --> 25:12.330
What was Jamie like as a boy?

25:12.470 --> 25:13.926
- Oh...
- Ugh.

25:14.010 --> 25:16.672
Best clear away the cobwebs

25:16.760 --> 25:18.637
if ye're to remember
anything from that time.

25:20.600 --> 25:24.229
Well, then, there was a time

25:24.310 --> 25:27.359
when wee_Jam_ie was sent off
to foster With hIS Uncle Dougal.

25:27.650 --> 25:28.639
Christ.

25:28.770 --> 25:30.647
He was around 14 or so.

25:30.780 --> 25:32.065
Dougal had four daughters.

25:32.150 --> 25:35.404
And Tabitha was the first girl
that Jamie ever kissed.

25:35.820 --> 25:37.731
She was the first girl to ever kiss me.

25:38.910 --> 25:42.744
I was carrying two pails of milk for her,

25:42.830 --> 25:46.322
and Tib took me by the ears, kissed me.

25:48.380 --> 25:49.369
Mind you, I spilled the milk.

25:50.920 --> 25:52.660
A memorable first experience.

25:52.760 --> 25:55.752
And my mother caught us
and told Dougal about it.

25:55.840 --> 25:58.001
Aye, so the next morning,

25:58.550 --> 26:01.462
Jamie wakes up to find Dougal
standing over him.

26:02.100 --> 26:04.591
They had a very pleasant conversation.

26:05.270 --> 26:08.808
Dougal says that he would hate
to think that his nephew

26:08.900 --> 26:11.437
could take advantage
of his daughter's feelings.

26:12.400 --> 26:13.856
That doesn't sound so bad.

26:13.940 --> 26:16.488
Aye, but the whole time
that Dougal was talking,

26:16.570 --> 26:18.276
he had one hand on his dirk,

26:18.700 --> 26:20.691
and the other one resting
on Jamie's bollocks.

26:22.410 --> 26:25.038
I didna look at a lass again
until I was 16.

26:25.660 --> 26:28.629
Great. I want to hear
more of these stories.

26:28.710 --> 26:30.621
Plenty more
where that came from, lad.

26:31.800 --> 26:34.041
I think that's enough stories
for one night.

26:34.840 --> 26:37.547
It's good to have family
around the table again.

26:37.680 --> 26:38.669
Aye.

26:39.590 --> 26:41.808
I'll go fetch us
some more wood for the fire.

26:49.770 --> 26:51.055
You'll never guess who I met.

26:51.730 --> 26:52.936
Um...

26:53.020 --> 26:54.021
King George?

26:54.480 --> 26:55.481
Warm.

26:56.110 --> 26:57.270
George Washington.

26:58.780 --> 27:00.156
That's amazing.

27:00.820 --> 27:03.732
I'd love to hear more about it,
but I'm exhausted.

27:04.120 --> 27:05.940
If you'll excuse me, I'm gonna go to bed.

27:06.040 --> 27:07.826
- Good night.
- Good night, lass.

27:08.120 --> 27:09.826
Of course, darling. I'll...

27:09.920 --> 27:11.569
I'll walk you to the shelter.

27:12.380 --> 27:13.745
I can check in on Lizzie.

27:14.630 --> 27:17.542
It's a shame she wasn't feeling
well enough to join us.

27:17.630 --> 27:19.837
The lass reminds me of yer mother.

27:21.680 --> 27:22.749
Same eyes.

27:24.180 --> 27:25.386
Aye, she does.

27:27.430 --> 27:28.840
And she's here.

27:31.400 --> 27:34.221
Ye've suffered enough pain in yer life.

27:35.110 --> 27:36.566
I'm glad for ye, lad.

27:36.650 --> 27:38.140
I just hope she can...

27:39.150 --> 27:41.061
feel this place is her home.

27:41.950 --> 27:43.190
She's still a stranger.

27:44.160 --> 27:45.536
Give her time.

27:45.620 --> 27:46.689
She'll come to know ye.

27:54.880 --> 27:56.757
Checked in on Lizzie
again this morning,

27:56.840 --> 27:59.126
and in better light, it could be malaria.

28:00.010 --> 28:03.138
I think an infusion of Jesuit bark
will help with that.

28:04.760 --> 28:05.966
I hope so.

28:07.560 --> 28:09.130
She's been a good friend to me.

28:10.480 --> 28:11.629
Hmm.

28:24.320 --> 28:25.366
Daddy knew.

28:30.040 --> 28:31.405
That you came back.

28:37.340 --> 28:40.002
I saw the obituary on his desk years ago.

28:40.340 --> 28:42.797
I didn't realise what it was at the time,

28:42.880 --> 28:46.964
but I remembered it recently
when I found it again myself.

28:48.560 --> 28:50.596
He knew you came back to Jamie.

29:00.780 --> 29:02.850
Frank was an astute man.

29:07.660 --> 29:09.537
He always knew my heart was here.

29:10.120 --> 29:11.690
I can see it, too.

29:14.370 --> 29:16.418
I see why you had to come back to Jamie.

29:24.630 --> 29:26.427
It's quite a lot to take in...

29:26.970 --> 29:27.959
being here.

29:29.180 --> 29:30.340
It was for me.

29:32.430 --> 29:33.886
It's quite overwhelming.

29:37.940 --> 29:38.929
Damn it!

29:39.110 --> 29:40.099
God.

29:41.610 --> 29:44.067
It's all right. It's all right.
Let me help.

29:45.280 --> 29:46.269
Hey.

29:48.530 --> 29:50.828
You know, you can talk to me about Roger.

29:52.040 --> 29:53.075
He's gone.

29:54.620 --> 29:56.326
There's nothing I can do about that now.

29:57.460 --> 29:59.416
It's not as if I can phone him.

30:14.930 --> 30:16.898
Spend it wisely. Next.

30:17.980 --> 30:19.516
Mr MacKenzie.

30:22.440 --> 30:23.896
Back to Carolina for you, is it?

30:23.990 --> 30:26.390
As soon as I can make _
my way aboard another ship.

30:27.110 --> 30:28.941
You have Danu. I have Eros.

30:31.660 --> 30:33.696
Forgive me, Captain,
but I wondered ifI may have

30:33.790 --> 30:37.419
one or two of those small gems
instead of coin as wages.

30:38.630 --> 30:39.745
Huh.

30:41.840 --> 30:43.080
Mmm...

30:45.220 --> 30:46.255
The smaller ones, perhaps.

30:53.850 --> 30:55.886
Eros must be a difficult lord to serve.

30:59.770 --> 31:01.010
Always a lassie.

31:03.980 --> 31:04.969
Next.

31:33.810 --> 31:34.799
Thanks.

32:00.420 --> 32:01.455
Safe travels.

32:33.910 --> 32:34.899
Christ.

32:36.490 --> 32:38.538
_ Where in God's name
did ye learn to shoot like that?

32:38.870 --> 32:39.859
My father.

32:42.000 --> 32:42.989
Frank.

32:44.880 --> 32:46.029
I ken his name.

32:47.550 --> 32:49.415
Yer mother told me about him.

32:50.170 --> 32:51.159
Yeah.

32:52.130 --> 32:55.133
He and I would camp out,
and he taught me to shoot.

32:55.600 --> 32:56.589
So...

33:08.440 --> 33:13.059
It's a far cry from
the still cellar at Leoch.

33:13.700 --> 33:15.236
It does make whisky, though.

33:15.320 --> 33:16.446
Of a sort.

33:18.580 --> 33:21.492
The farmers from
the Ridge supply the barley

33:21.580 --> 33:23.616
and help distribute the liquor.

33:27.250 --> 33:30.162
So, does everyone always
call you "Young" Ian?

33:30.960 --> 33:33.929
When I was a bairn, it was "Wee" Ian.

33:35.300 --> 33:36.790
Everyone always just calls me "Bree."

33:40.520 --> 33:43.387
Is that what you call her
when you shorten her name?

33:43.520 --> 33:44.509
Aye.

33:46.100 --> 33:47.647
Something wrong with Bree?

33:49.150 --> 33:52.358
No, it's a Scots word.

33:55.780 --> 33:57.270
It doesna translate.

34:12.840 --> 34:14.410
A bree means a disturbance?

34:14.510 --> 34:15.499
Aye.

34:15.970 --> 34:17.039
Among other things.

34:17.140 --> 34:18.960
Well, you could have told her that.

34:19.760 --> 34:22.718
She's not some fragile piece of glass
that can break, you know.

34:23.100 --> 34:24.590
I dinna want to hurt the lass.

34:26.140 --> 34:30.349
She's clearly heartsick over this Roger.

34:32.940 --> 34:34.567
I ken how she feels.

34:36.950 --> 34:40.488
When I thought I'd lost you forever,
breathing was a chore.

34:42.910 --> 34:44.571
That's just a part of it.

34:45.710 --> 34:47.246
She doesn't want to hurt you.

34:48.210 --> 34:50.997
I've watched the two of you
the last few weeks

34:51.090 --> 34:53.331
tiptoeing around talking about Frank.

34:57.220 --> 34:59.506
Perhaps you should
take her hunting with you.

35:00.680 --> 35:02.841
It would take her mind off Roger,

35:03.220 --> 35:05.848
and you'd have some time
to spend together alone.

35:47.810 --> 35:48.799
Bnanna.

36:01.660 --> 36:03.116
I'll be hunting up the mountain.

36:04.030 --> 36:05.440
Will ye come wi' me, lass?

36:23.340 --> 36:25.501
So, what are we hunting?

36:27.350 --> 36:28.339
Bees.

36:30.230 --> 36:31.299
Bees?

36:32.190 --> 36:33.396
How do you hunt bees?

36:34.360 --> 36:35.679
Look for flowers.

36:39.940 --> 36:45.947
It's good to spend time with you,
a /eannan, m’annsachd.

36:46.530 --> 36:47.906
You called me that before.

36:48.450 --> 36:50.577
What does that mean,
”a /eannan ”.7

36:51.000 --> 36:52.490
And the other word you said?

36:53.710 --> 36:54.916
It means...

36:56.540 --> 36:57.746
Means my darling.

37:01.510 --> 37:03.501
M’ annsacho;
my blessing.

37:29.910 --> 37:30.899
Look.

37:38.880 --> 37:40.086
Ah.

37:48.050 --> 37:52.168
See, the hummingbirds like to drink
from the long-throated flowers,

37:52.270 --> 37:54.761
but the bees canna get inside.

37:55.390 --> 38:00.430
They like the broad,
flat flowers like these.

38:04.780 --> 38:08.568
They light on them and wallow
till they're all covered over wi' yellow.

38:12.040 --> 38:13.530
Watch.

38:14.660 --> 38:16.287
See which direction they go.

38:30.760 --> 38:31.966
A tree.

38:33.220 --> 38:34.266
That's good.

38:34.890 --> 38:38.849
Sometimes they hive among the rocks,
and then there's little ye can do.

38:40.820 --> 38:43.641
Now, it's best to wait until dark,

38:44.240 --> 38:46.731
for then all the swarm
will be inside the hive.

38:47.530 --> 38:48.940
How will you move the hive?

38:49.990 --> 38:52.117
Once all the bees
have gone to their rest...

38:53.160 --> 38:54.149
I'll...

38:56.160 --> 38:57.616
I'll blow a bit 0' smoke...

38:59.330 --> 39:01.286
into the hive, keep them stunned.

39:04.550 --> 39:07.212
And then wrap it in my bag.

39:09.470 --> 39:12.428
Then once we've returned home, ye'll see.

39:13.220 --> 39:16.269
I'll place it in a bee gum,
and come the morning,

39:16.350 --> 39:20.059
the bees will venture out,
looking around for the nearest flowers.

39:22.520 --> 39:24.852
Won't they realise
they aren't in their proper place?

39:26.940 --> 39:28.316
And what'll they do about it?

39:29.070 --> 39:33.188
They've no means to find their way back
and no home left here to come back to.

39:34.830 --> 39:35.819
Nah.

39:37.160 --> 39:39.037
Nay, they'll be content.

39:41.670 --> 39:44.082
Content in their new home.

39:47.760 --> 39:49.125
I have a home.

39:52.180 --> 39:54.171
I dinna wish to replace your father.

39:54.850 --> 39:56.010
He was a good man.

39:57.020 --> 39:59.511
I feel disloyal to him
even being here with you.

40:02.940 --> 40:04.180
I'm grateful to him.

40:06.190 --> 40:10.308
He raised you for yer mother's sake,
a child of another man...

40:11.450 --> 40:13.236
a man he had no cause to love.

40:15.790 --> 40:17.155
He stood by you both.

40:18.660 --> 40:19.706
And he loved you...

40:20.960 --> 40:22.916
even though he didna see himself in you.

40:30.880 --> 40:32.370
I had to give you to him.

40:33.590 --> 40:35.501
Though I canna say I'm sorry
ye came back to me.

40:38.270 --> 40:39.976
Sure I'm not a bree?

40:40.940 --> 40:41.929
Disturbance, huh?

40:43.690 --> 40:45.055
Murtagh told me.

40:47.190 --> 40:48.646
Aye, ye are.

40:49.440 --> 40:51.396
As was yer mother before ye, but...

40:53.820 --> 40:55.060
Ye're one I welcome.

40:59.540 --> 41:00.996
Ye're my flesh and blood.

41:03.960 --> 41:06.167
Since ye returned to me,
I'm finding ye're my...

41:06.750 --> 41:08.411
My heart and soul as well.

41:10.340 --> 41:11.329
So...

41:12.510 --> 41:16.344
I will keep calling ye Bree,
if ye dinna mind it.

41:19.970 --> 41:21.631
I don't know what to call you.

41:25.650 --> 41:29.643
You can call me Da, if ye like.

41:30.030 --> 41:31.019
Da?

41:31.570 --> 41:32.696
Is that Gaelic?

41:34.240 --> 41:35.229
No.

41:36.030 --> 41:37.110
It's only...

41:39.160 --> 41:40.320
It's only simple.

41:57.930 --> 41:59.090
Welcome back.

42:04.060 --> 42:05.891
I'll put the kettle on, shall I?

42:14.650 --> 42:15.696
Good job.

42:16.490 --> 42:17.525
You too.

42:23.330 --> 42:24.740
Aye, look at that.

42:49.650 --> 42:50.856
Can't sleep?

42:53.230 --> 42:54.231
No.

43:02.620 --> 43:04.360
Something bothering you?

43:06.120 --> 43:07.530
Och.

43:10.080 --> 43:11.877
Just a foolish regret.

43:14.050 --> 43:16.257
These past few weeks with our daughter...

43:17.720 --> 43:19.460
means so much to me.

43:21.890 --> 43:23.255
Must we lose her?

43:25.600 --> 43:28.342
I dinna want her to return
to her own time, Sassenach.

43:31.520 --> 43:33.511
I wish she could stay here too.

43:36.900 --> 43:39.061
For a while at least...

43:40.950 --> 43:42.269
but not forever.

43:43.990 --> 43:46.322
She belongs back in her time.

43:47.500 --> 43:48.819
It's safer there.

43:49.460 --> 43:51.451
There's more opportunities for her.

43:55.550 --> 43:57.836
I know I mustn't grieve for it.

44:05.010 --> 44:06.261
She...

44:10.140 --> 44:11.801
She smiles in her sleep...

44:12.860 --> 44:14.054
as ye say I do.

44:17.150 --> 44:19.698
I remember Jenny

44:20.570 --> 44:23.733
bending over each of her newborn bairns,

44:24.620 --> 44:27.487
watching them for hours.

44:30.410 --> 44:33.163
I could watch Brianna like that
and never tire of it.

44:37.210 --> 44:38.666
She's a gift...

44:42.630 --> 44:43.836
from me to you...

44:46.970 --> 44:48.631
and you to me.

44:54.230 --> 44:55.766
And she called me Da.

45:25.090 --> 45:26.341
Mistress.

45:28.060 --> 45:29.550
Ye're awake so early.

45:30.640 --> 45:31.800
I couldn't sleep.

45:33.190 --> 45:35.841
I thought I heard ye crying in the night.

45:36.810 --> 45:37.890
Are you all right?

45:39.150 --> 45:40.435
Just a bad dream.

45:41.110 --> 45:42.270
Another one?

45:43.200 --> 45:44.690
Ye've been having so many.

45:44.780 --> 45:46.691
Lizzie, I'm fine. Honest.

45:49.700 --> 45:50.985
Very well, then.

45:52.620 --> 45:56.454
If ye dinna mind, I'll be going with Ian
to the mill today.

45:56.540 --> 45:57.529
Of course.

45:57.710 --> 45:59.416
I'm gonna pick herbs with my mother.

45:59.500 --> 46:00.740
I'll see you in a while?

46:28.200 --> 46:31.738
Now, I know you're missing Roger.

46:32.740 --> 46:34.458
There's something else, isn't there?

46:39.500 --> 46:41.548
I wondered if you could still do that.

46:42.840 --> 46:43.829
Do what?

46:43.920 --> 46:45.080
Read my mind.

46:46.630 --> 46:47.927
Sort of hoped you could.

46:50.220 --> 46:53.053
Well, I expect
I'm a little out of practice.

46:57.140 --> 46:58.346
Give me a moment.

47:11.990 --> 47:13.400
How far along are you?

47:17.790 --> 47:18.996
About two months.

47:22.090 --> 47:24.331
Didn't you or Roger
think to use any precautions?

47:25.380 --> 47:28.213
I didn't think I needed
to pack condoms, Mama.

47:30.430 --> 47:31.419
Of course.

47:33.100 --> 47:35.762
I don't suppose
Roger knows about any of this...

47:37.020 --> 47:38.976
given that he left so soon after?

47:41.100 --> 47:42.101
Well, um...

47:47.360 --> 47:49.021
It might not be Roger's.

47:51.910 --> 47:52.979
What?

47:56.330 --> 47:58.207
It might not be Roger's baby.

48:04.250 --> 48:05.376
All right.

48:08.050 --> 48:11.213
Then whose?

48:18.480 --> 48:19.765
Um...

48:22.650 --> 48:23.719
There was...

48:25.770 --> 48:26.976
this man...

48:28.400 --> 48:30.311
at the Willow Tree Tavern.

48:31.820 --> 48:33.731
We started talking, and...

48:37.410 --> 48:38.536
And...

48:43.250 --> 48:44.990
And then I didn't fight him.

48:47.550 --> 48:49.256
I didn't fight him hard enough.

48:49.340 --> 48:50.910
Why the hell didn't I fight him?

48:51.220 --> 48:54.132
Brianna. Oh, Brianna.

48:56.470 --> 48:57.926
No, it's not your fault.

49:02.270 --> 49:03.760
Oh, my baby.

49:06.060 --> 49:07.391
My baby.

49:28.500 --> 49:29.626
How...

49:31.090 --> 49:32.660
How certain are you that...

49:34.340 --> 49:36.251
Well, that the baby isn't Roger's?

49:39.010 --> 49:40.386
Well, he didn't...

49:41.730 --> 49:44.893
I mean, Roger didn't, um...

49:46.940 --> 49:47.975
Withdrawal method.

49:52.320 --> 49:54.026
And when did the...

49:57.740 --> 49:59.116
It was the same night.

50:02.620 --> 50:03.700
Oh, Brianna.

50:15.880 --> 50:17.336
I need to talk to you.

50:19.220 --> 50:20.380
About Brianna.

50:29.230 --> 50:30.219
She wants to leave.

50:36.990 --> 50:37.979
No.

50:47.290 --> 50:48.370
What?

50:57.220 --> 50:58.209
She was raped.

51:01.300 --> 51:02.506
In Wilmington.

51:03.430 --> 51:04.920
Right after Roger left.

51:06.730 --> 51:08.516
She only just told me today.

51:15.650 --> 51:17.026
But there's something else.

51:22.280 --> 51:23.486
She's pregnant.

51:59.030 --> 52:01.908
Lizzie. What's the matter?

52:02.570 --> 52:03.776
It's him.

52:04.790 --> 52:07.190
Lord, it's... It's him.

52:07.290 --> 52:08.325
VVho?

52:46.120 --> 52:47.189
Uncle Jamie.

52:47.330 --> 52:48.695
Ian? Lizzie?

52:49.500 --> 52:50.489
What's wrong?

52:50.660 --> 52:52.662
She saw a man
that put a fright into her, Uncle.

52:52.750 --> 52:54.320
Near the road, sir.

52:55.000 --> 52:56.331
She kent him.

52:56.420 --> 52:57.409
Seen him before...

52:57.960 --> 52:59.257
with Brianna.

53:00.010 --> 53:00.999
And?

53:01.090 --> 53:02.079
At Wilmington.

53:02.840 --> 53:04.580
A brute of a man, he was.

53:05.180 --> 53:06.386
Brianna was afraid of him.

53:07.310 --> 53:10.347
He came close to her...

53:11.270 --> 53:13.306
and held her by the arms.

53:14.060 --> 53:15.436
Took her away with him.

53:17.480 --> 53:18.890
And you let her go wi' him?

53:18.980 --> 53:22.859
I should have gone after her,
but I was afraid, sir.

53:23.610 --> 53:25.157
May God forgive me.

53:28.790 --> 53:29.779
She...

53:31.040 --> 53:33.747
She didna return nigh till dawn.

53:35.170 --> 53:38.549
She had bruises,
and her nose was bleeding.

53:39.500 --> 53:40.501
And...

53:41.210 --> 53:43.508
There was blood on her petticoats.

53:44.590 --> 53:45.636
And...

53:46.850 --> 53:49.000
I could smell him on her.

53:50.100 --> 53:52.056
His seed.

53:54.440 --> 53:57.147
She was a virgin when he took her.

53:58.150 --> 53:59.811
I am her maid, sir.

54:00.530 --> 54:01.645
I saw the blood.

54:03.280 --> 54:04.269
And now he's come after her--

54:04.360 --> 54:06.271
Are ye sure this is the same man
who attacked her?

54:06.360 --> 54:07.657
I'm sure of it.

54:08.370 --> 54:09.860
D'ye think he's come to claim her?

54:09.950 --> 54:11.190
Go to the cabin.

54:11.540 --> 54:13.155
Dinna breathe a word of this
to my wife or daughter.

54:13.250 --> 54:14.239
You understand?

54:14.460 --> 54:15.916
O clear Mother.

54:16.000 --> 54:17.206
O blessed Mother, what have I done?

54:17.290 --> 54:19.497
Go! Ian, see her home.

54:30.640 --> 54:31.766
Need some help?

54:43.280 --> 54:44.349
Where did you get this?

54:47.570 --> 54:50.027
Brianna, tell me.

54:54.330 --> 54:55.570
Stephen Bonnet?

55:00.540 --> 55:01.529
He's the man who...

55:05.800 --> 55:09.964
I saw him with your ring,
and I offered to buy it from him.

55:13.680 --> 55:14.806
That's when it happened?

55:17.600 --> 55:18.976
Why did you not tell me this?

55:19.060 --> 55:20.266
I couldn't.

55:21.900 --> 55:23.720
Ian told me about
what happened on the river.

55:24.730 --> 55:26.482
And I knew that you would feel awful

55:26.570 --> 55:28.310
for what happened to me
because of the ring,

55:28.410 --> 55:31.777
and Jamie would blame himself
because he helped Bonnet escape.

55:32.700 --> 55:34.611
If he knows, he'll try to find Bonnet.

55:35.450 --> 55:37.156
And I can't let him do that.

55:37.750 --> 55:39.820
You've met the man, Mama.
You know what he's like.

55:41.500 --> 55:43.912
You have to promise me
to keep this to yourself.

55:44.050 --> 55:45.415
- No_.
- Promise.

55:55.390 --> 55:56.630
Good day, sir.

55:56.770 --> 55:58.260
